Dear Lili,  I followed you BECAUSE you opened your heart up and let out some of your insecurities and truth. THANK YOU for sharing that part of you with the world and I am proud of you for being brave enough to talk about it. It is a sad world full of sad people who cannot learn to love and accept themselves by inner-reflection. And instead, seek to outwardly achieve it by pushing others down. We just have to love those people harder, even when it hurts. Because something in them has truly been broken to be jealous of another person, even when they come forth to say that THEY, TOO - feel the way we ALL do sometimes. You have the hardest job of all, Lili. Because YOUR life and career - the same as anyone in the entertainment industry, is often priced at the value of your appearance rather than your skills - which are many. People not part of that industry often don’t understand and cannot fathom, the amount of people from day to day who have something diminishing to say about you or your body. And it can truly destroy your esteem. We see celebrities like Demi Lovato and CHEER FOR HER when she makes a come back, rather than applaud her work and effort and make her feel valued TO BEGIN WITH, so that she wouldn’t feel so alone in her hurt, unheard, and so worthless. And this is what is wrong with the world. We have stopped trying to bond and relate to one another in good times and bad and help each other. We just sit back and take credit for supporting people when they rise from the WORST times in their lives, because everybody ‘loves a winner’, and nobody minds riding off of someone’s triumph even if they achieved it, from the same failure those people caused. Lili, your feelings ARE valid. Don’t you dare let anyone tell you that they aren’t. I do not know you, and you have no reason to trust me - but the point remains. I want you to know that if you EVER need someone to talk to, I am happy to listen and offer support and just help lift you up. We have to learn how to help each other, periodt. 👌🏼
